{"timestamp": "2026-05-22 12:01:49,899", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T12:01:49.899501\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Develop clearing mechanics: detect and clear full lines (Tetris) and match-3 groups (Bejeweled) with chain reactions\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\nfrom enum import Enum, auto\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\\nfrom typing import List, Optional, Tuple, Dict\\n\\n# Gem Types / Colors\\nclass GemColor(Enum):\\n    RED    = auto()\\n    GREEN  = auto()\\n    BLUE   = auto()\\n    YELLOW = auto()\\n    ORANGE = auto()\\n    PURPLE = auto()\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass Gem:\\n    color: GemColor\\n\\n# Tetromino Types\\nclass TetrominoType(Enum):\\n    I = auto()\\n    O = auto()\\n    T = auto()\\n    S = auto()\\n    Z = auto()\\n    J = auto()\\n    L = au...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. There’s no single method that runs both Tetris line clearance and Bejeweled chain‐reaction clearance in one pass, making it awkward to hook into the game loop.\\n2. Scoring is missing: we need to return number of lines cleared, gems cleared, and optionally a combined score or chain multiplier.\\n3. `clear_full_lines()` may skip multiple clears in the same column because it increments the row index even after a clear and shift.\\n4. `find_matches()` only finds exact triples; it doesn’t detect longer runs (4+ in a row) as single matches.\\n5. No documentation/comments on how to use the clearing flow from the main game loop.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\nfrom enum import Enum, auto\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\\nfrom typing import List, Optional, Tuple, Dict, Set\\n\\n# Gem Types / Colors\\nclass GemColor(Enum):\\n    RED    = auto()\\n    GREEN  = auto()\\n    BLUE   = auto()\\n    YELLOW = auto()\\n    ORANGE = auto()\\n    PURPLE = auto()\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass Gem:\\n    color: GemColor\\n\\n# Tetromino Types\\nclass TetrominoType(Enum):\\n    I = auto()\\n    O = auto()\\n    T = auto()\\n    S = auto()\\n    Z = auto()\\n    J = auto()\\n    L = auto()\\n\\n# Rotation states: List of (x, y) offsets relative to a pivot (0,0)\\nTETROMINO_SHAPES: Dict[TetrominoType, List[List[Tuple[int,int]]]] = {\\n    # ... same as before ...\\n}\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass Tetromino:\\n    type: TetrominoType\\n    rotation: int = 0         # 0–3 index into rotation states\\n    x: int = 0                # column pivot\\n    y: int = 0                # row pivot\\n\\n    def current_blocks(self) -> List[Tuple[int,int]]:\\n        shape = TETROMINO_SHAPES[self.type][self.rotation % 4]\\n        return [(self.x + dx, self.y + dy) for dx, dy in shape]\\n\\n    def rotate(self, clockwise: bool = True) -> None:\\n        self.rotation = (self.rotation + (1 if clockwise else -1)) % 4\\n\\nclass Grid:\\n    def __init__(self, width: int = 10, height: int = 20):\\n        self.width = width\\n        self.height = height\\n        self.cells: List[List[Optional[Gem]]] = [\\n            [None]*width for _ in range(height)\\n        ]\\n\\n    def in_bounds(self, x: int, y: int) -> bool:\\n        return 0 <= x < self.width and 0 <= y < self.height\\n\\n    def get_cell(self, x: int, y: int) -> Optional[Gem]:\\n        return self.cells[y][x] if self.in_bounds(x, y) else None\\n\\n    def set_cell(self, x: int, y: int, gem: Optional[Gem]) -> None:\\n        if self.in_bounds(x, y):\\n            self.cells[y][x] = gem\\n\\n    def clear_cell(self, x: int, y: int) -> None:\\n        if self.in_bounds(x, y):\\n            self.cells[y][x] = None\\n\\n    def reset(self) -> None:\\n        for y in range(self.height):\\n            for x in range(self.width):\\n                self.cells[y][x] = None\\n\\n    def clear_full_lines(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Clears all full horizontal lines.\\n        Returns the number of lines cleared.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        lines_cleared = 0\\n        # Start from bottom row upward\\n        y = self.height - 1\\n        while y >= 0:\\n            if all(self.cells[y][x] is not None for x in range(self.width)):\\n                # Remove this line\\n                del self.cells[y]\\n                # Insert empty line at top\\n                self.cells.insert(0, [None]*self.width)\\n                lines_cleared += 1\\n                # Do not decrement y so we re-check the row that just shifted down\\n            else:\\n                y -= 1\\n        return lines_cleared\\n\\n    def find_matches(self) -> Set[Tuple[int, int]]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Finds all contiguous horizontal or vertical runs of length >= 3.\\n        Returns a set of (x,y) positions that should be cleared.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matched: Set[Tuple[int,int]] = set()\\n\\n        # Horizontal scanning\\n        for y in range(self.height):\\n            x = 0\\n            while x < self.width:\\n                start = x\\n                gem = self.get_cell(x, y)\\n                if gem is None:\\n                    x += 1\\n                    continue\\n                # run until different or out of bounds\\n                while x < self.width and self.get_cell(x, y) and self.get_cell(x, y).color == gem.color:\\n                    x += 1\\n                length = x - start\\n                if length >= 3:\\n                    for px in range(start, x):\\n                        matched.add((px, y))\\n                # continue scanning from current x\\n\\n        # Vertical scanning\\n        for x in range(self.width):\\n            y = 0\\n            while y < self.height:\\n                start = y\\n                gem = self.get_cell(x, y)\\n                if gem is None:\\n                    y += 1\\n                    continue\\n                while y < self.height and self.get_cell(x, y) and self.get_cell(x, y).color == gem.color:\\n                    y += 1\\n                length = y - start\\n                if length >= 3:\\n                    for py in range(start, y):\\n                        matched.add((x, py))\\n        return matched\\n\\n    def clear_matches(self, matches: Set[Tuple[int,int]]) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Clears exactly the provided match coordinates.\\n        Returns number of gems cleared.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        count = 0\\n        for x, y in matches:\\n            if self.get_cell(x, y) is not None:\\n                self.clear_cell(x, y)\\n                count += 1\\n        return count\\n\\n    def apply_gravity(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Gems fall straight down to fill empty spaces.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x in range(self.width):\\n            stack = [self.cells[y][x] for y in range(self.height) if self.cells[y][x] is not None]\\n            empties = [None] * (self.height - len(stack))\\n            col = empties + stack\\n            for y in range(self.height):\\n                self.cells[y][x] = col[y]\\n\\n    def resolve_chains(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Runs repeated match detection + gravity until no more matches.\\n        Returns total gems cleared in chain.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        total = 0\\n        while True:\\n            matches = self.find_matches()\\n            if not matches:\\n                break\\n            total += self.clear_matches(matches)\\n            self.apply_gravity()\\n        return total\\n\\n    def clear_tetris_and_bejeweled(self) -> Dict[str, int]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Performs one full clearing step:\\n          1) Clears all full lines (Tetris)\\n          2) Applies gravity\\n          3) Clears all match-3+ groups (Bejeweled) repeatedly\\n        Returns a dict with:\\n          'lines_cleared', 'gems_cleared', 'total_score'\\n        Scoring formula (example):\\n          100 points per line, 50 points per gem, 1.5x bonus per chain round.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # 1) Tetris lines\\n        lines = self.clear_full_lines()\\n        # 2) Gravity after lines\\n        self.apply_gravity()\\n        # 3) Bejeweled chains\\n        gems = 0\\n        chain_round = 0\\n        chain_score = 0.0\\n        while True:\\n            matches = self.find_matches()\\n            if not matches:\\n                break\\n            cleared = self.clear_matches(matches)\\n            gems += cleared\\n            self.apply_gravity()\\n            chain_round += 1\\n            chain_score += cleared * 50 * (1.0 + 0.5*(chain_round-1))\\n        # Total score\\n        total_score = lines * 100 + int(chain_score)\\n        return {\\n            'lines_cleared': lines,\\n            'gems_cleared': gems,\\n            'total_score': total_score\\n        }\\n```\\nDetailed usage:\\n- Lock tetromino into the grid by setting appropriate `Gem(color)` in each cell.\\n- Then call `clear_tetris_and_bejeweled()` each frame after locking to get clear counts and score.\\n- Integrate its returned dict into your game’s running score and UI display.\"}"}
